Reasoning: The paper presents a method for learning control policies that can operate under unknown dynamic models, which is a problem commonly addressed in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves leveraging a large number of training examples generated using a physical simulator, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The system also involves predicting the dynamics model parameters online, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the system on a variety of tasks, including block-throwing of a manipulator, which suggests the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
